   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Click the Batch Cullet Weighing tab at the top of the screen to display the main Batch Cullet Weighing screen, shown below.  </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Click the down arrow button to display the popup window to navigate to the following operation screens, which are shown on the following pages:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Status – provides an overview regarding the current weighing cycle of the scales</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Formula - clicking the button opens a Formula screen where the cullet ratio is entered</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Consumption – the production data for today and the previous 14 days are displayed</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Timer - used to adjust scale and plant timers for the Integration system equipment</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Preselection – used to select the active formula </li>
      </ul>
      <note type="note" id="note_pkn_l2g_vcc" class="- topic/note ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">The Integration system screen also allows these operations, as well as others. For
            details, refer to SBS-OP-006 Operating the Integration System.</p>
